  • Method Details

    • isEqualTo

      public void isEqualTo(@Nullable String expected)
      Checks that the actual value is equal to the given sequence (while ignoring case). For the purposes of this comparison, two strings are equal if either of the following is true:
      • They are equal according to String.equalsIgnoreCase(java.lang.String). (In Kotlin terms: They are equal according to actual.equals(expected, ignoreCase = true).)
      • They are both null.

      Example: "abc" is equal to "ABC", but not to "abcd".

    • isNotEqualTo

      public void isNotEqualTo(@Nullable String other)
      Checks that the actual value is not equal to the given string (while ignoring case). The meaning of equality is the same as for the isEqualTo(java.lang.String) method.
